  "summaries": [
    {
      "id": 827168,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "A flaw in Node.js HTTP request handling causes an uncaught `TypeError` when a request is received with a header named `__proto__` and the application accesses `req.headersDistinct`.\n\nWhen this occurs, `dest[\"__proto__\"]` resolves to `Object.prototype` rather than `undefined`, causing `.push()` to be called on a non-array. This exception is thrown synchronously inside a property getter and cannot be intercepted by `error` event listeners, meaning it cannot be handled without wrapping every `req.headersDistinct` access in a `try/catch`.\n\n* This vulnerability affects all Node.js HTTP servers on **20.x, 22.x, 24.x, and v25.x** ",
